New Records: Ruben Trumpelmann ended with career-best figures of 4-21 as Namibia skittle Oman for a paltry total of 109 runs
Key Match Events: Ruben Trumpelmann dismisses Oman opener Kashyap Prajapati and captain Aqib Ilyas off the first two balls of the match
David Wiese picks up two wickets, and so does skipper Erasmus
Namibia finally find some much-needed boundaries as the runs needed trickle down to 18
Mehran Khan's Fab Final Over Takes Match Into Super Over
Namibia Smack 21 Runs In Super Over
Wiese Calmly Bowls Namibia To Super Over Win
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia captain Gerhard Erasmus: 'Looks a good wicket and there's some rain around later maybe. We gotta go out there and show what we are about.'
Oman captain Aqib Ilyas: 'It's good to bat on a fresh wicket and the ball will come on nicely in the night.'
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese is named the Player Of The Match for his all-round heroics for Namibia
Aqib Ilyas: 'Credit goes to Namibia. Credit goes to Trumpelmann for the way he executed, and then our batters adjusted well.'
Gerhard Erasmus: 'Difficult to get momentum through the innings, we tried by getting the singles and doubles but every now and then we needed those boundaries which were difficult to execute.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a bonafide low-scoring thriller
The two teams have faced off six times in T20 internationals, with Namibia winning four matches to Oman's two
Namibia have progressed to their third consecutive T20 World Cup on the back of an undefeated campaign at the Africa qualifier
